            <thetext>Hi,

I&#39;m working on a widget that relies on an editable &lt;DIV&gt; (I&#39;m using the contentEditable attribute). 

It works great except when I press the SPACE key in the editable region (nothing is written on the screen). The problem occurs because the private method &quot;__preventScrollWhenFocused&quot; of the qx.ui.root.Abstract class is triggered.

For the moment (and according to this method), the SPACE key press is allowed when the contentElement is a textfield or a textarea but not when it contains an &quot;editable&quot; node. 

It would be nice to add another condition in this method that allows pressing the SPACE key for this special case.

Best,

Benoît.</thetext>
